@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

Introduction
------------

GuideTool is an AmigaGuide (TM) (Short: AG) Convert Tool. It is possible to
create automatically tables of contents, Indexes in alphabetic order, and
insertion of cross references ("link labels" in AG jargon) in an AG file.

Here is a short introduction for the impatient:

GuideTool 1.0 Copyright (C) 1995 by Reinhard Katzmann. All Rights Reserved
Usage: GuideTool FROM/A,TO/A,C=CONTENTFILE/K,X=XREFFILE/K,CONTENTS/S,INDEX/S,
                 XREF/S,MAKECONT/S,MAKEXREF/S,L=LABELSIZE/K/N,R=XREFSIZE/K/N,ILN=INNERLINKS/S

FROM: Source file, usually the AG file you want to work on. Special case:
      INDEX, there it is the xref (= cross reference)) file.

TO: Output file: Dependant from the switch you choose this is the contentfile,
    the xreffile or the indexfile being written as AG index file or AG contents
    file or being the AG file written with link labels.

remark: All created files are written in ASCII format.

C=CONTENTFILE/K: contents file for reading when you use the switvh CONTENTS

X=XREFFILE/K: xref file for reading when you use the switch XREF or INDEX

Switches: Only _ONE_ switch may be used at the same time.

CONTENTS/S: Saves the AG table of contents with the help of a contents file
            (as main node)
            
XREF/S: Save the AG File with all link labels with the help of a xref File
        and what could be found with the help of the search function 
        (see also XREF-Concept)

INDEX/S: Saves an AG index file  with the help of an INDEX file.

MAKECONT/S: Creates Contents file (own ASCII format, may be edited)

MAKEXREF/S: Creates XRef file (own ASCII format, may be edited)

L=LABELSIZE/K/N: The maximum size of a link label. Defaults to 60.

R=XREFSIZE/K/N: The maximum size of a cross reference. Defaults to 40.

ILN=INNERLINKS/S: Switch which enables that links with the same name but diff-
                  erent jump number are accepted (and more)

@endnode

