@node "History" "History"

V 0.7b
------

- First beta release with some bugs

V.0.8b
------

- Second beta release distributed to different people
- Removed some smaller bugs
- XREF function optimised for speed (new XREF-Conzept!)
- For gaining more speed only whole words are recognized (words which are
  separated by break symbols), f.e. "GUI" does no longer match with "GuideTool"
- the new XREF Concept also solves a few other problems
- Added Amigaguide DOkumentation in german
- Uses now "###" in the contents file to differ from upper and lower part
- Bug in MAKECONT: I forgot to include "###" at the beginning (actually I had
  forgotten to include the empy line)
- Bug in node recognition: "@node main\\n" was not recognized.
- Label comparisions were stupidly case sensitiv. Corrected
- Big Bug: Existing link labels had never been parsed (the function which 
  should to this was corrupt :-( )
  (Such as \@{".." link ".."}, in the XREF function)
- Created first Archive

V0.9b
-----

- Reduced memory usage (using new switches l=labelsize, r=xrefsize)
- Promptly forgotten to include the XREF-Concepts
- Now includes english documentation (as you can read ;-)
- Removed a "missing blank" bug in XREF function
- Word Wrapping concept added to XREF-Concept (suggestion from Magnus Holmgren)
- Now MAKEXREF recognizes \@{"label" link jump}
- On failure returns with error code 20
- XREF: Recongizes \@{"label" link jump} as a correct label
  (I had forgotten to update that section :-( )
- Fixed bug which caused small words within AG commands to disappear
BETA 2
- Improved output of MAKECONT and MAKEXREF (in columns)
- c/contents option can now be used together with MAKEXREF and XREF optionally
  (this allows to also add nodes into the XRef file)
- Bugfix in the link input function: \@{".." link ".."} is now ignored

V1.0
- made some minor changes to the documentation
- fixed some minor bugs

@endnode

